      "writtenOn": "2025-12-29T13:56:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this a normal condition or something that is so serious that should even abort the whole operation?\n\nReturning `false` and then logging at `severe` level seems counterintuitive: if it is normal and you expect this to happen, then it should be a debug or max warning. Alternatively, if this is serious, it should re-throw the exception (maybe `IllegalStateException`?) and not just return `false` as it was a normal flow.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 132,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 135,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "1b04cf70ecef76bb0b5ca993be68f0b6440b2cf7",
